Overview - Pamplona Funds



































Skip to content







Menu














Overview



Since its inception in 2005, Pamplona has raised five private equity funds with over €7 billion of capital commitments
In June 2014, Pamplona launched its fourth private equity fund, Pamplona Capital Partners IV, LP, with €3.0 billion of committed capital
The funds are managed by a team of professionals, comprising 13 nationalities, with extensive experience in private equity investing
We invest long-term capital in market-leading companies that are managed by exceptional management teams
We have a highly flexible investment strategy across a broad range of asset classes, geographical markets and industry sectors, in both public and private market situations
We invest primarily in Europe and North America
The private equity team is based in London and New York
In October 2015, Pamplona launched Pamplona TMT I, L.P., a dedicated fund with $1 billion of committed capital, which will make equity investments in technology, media and telecom (TMT) companies


























